description:
This is a 21 minute workout called '20 MIN HIIT Treadmill Workout' from the channel IBX Running.
The workout falls under Cardio/HIIT and Cardio/Treadmill.
It's suitable for Intermediate and Beginner fitness levels.
You'll need Treadmill for this workout.
The workout has a The Firestarter and The Warrior Workout vibe.
The technique difficulty is Intermediate and Beginner.
The effort required is Moderate and Challenging.

Original workout description: Coach Veronica is back with a 20 Minute HIIT Treadmill Workout!! We are hitting 60 seconds at a base pace before pushing for a minute and doing a 30 second hard push before coming back down to base. Get ready to get sweaty!

20:00 minutes of run and recovery intervals

All speeds and inclines are suggestions. Please stay safe and within your comfort zone!

Join our community of runners: http://www.ibxrunning.com
Merch: https://www.ibxrunning.com/store
IBX Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/ibxrunning/
Veronica's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/bodibyroni/
Rachael's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/bedopefitness/

00:00 - Intro
00:26 - Warm Up
03:24 - Workout!
18:20 - Cool Down

Workout Structure:
WARMUP: 3 minutes 
HIIT SECTION: Repeat 4 times
      BASE PACE: 1 minutes - 5.5 - 7.5 mph
      PUSH PACE: 1 minute - 6.0 - 8.0 mph
      HARD PUSH: 30 seconds - 6.5 - 8.5 mph
RECOVER: 1 minute
LONG PUSH: 4 minutes - 6.0 - 8.0 mph
Cooldown at the end!
